Remarks: NPG is in the process of getting rid of the "Bound Object" classification. Almost all are prints that are bound in books, albums, etc. Most of these are catalogued as “virtual objects”, since there is a corresponding record for the book or album that they’re bound within.
Two of NPG's 7 coins are not money and so might fit better under medal.
Sketchbooks, 2 pressed paper portraits and a few works by Chuck Close that defy classification
Selected this term over "transparencies" (http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300127478 ) because it falls under "direct positives" under "photographs"
